To configure a B trigger that occurs 5 events after an A trigger on CH1 for a Tektronix MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope, you need to set up a trigger sequence (A-B trigger) with the appropriate settings. This is typically done using the SCOPE:TRIGger:A:TYPE and SCOPE:TRIGger:B:EVENTS commands.

Here is a TekAutomate Steps UI flow to accomplish this:

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "id": "connect_scope",
      "title": "Connect to Oscilloscope"
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_trigger_type",
      "title": "Set Trigger Type to Sequence (A-B)",
      "params": {
        "command": "TRIG:A:TYPE SEQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_a_trigger_source",
      "title": "Set A Trigger Source to CH1",
      "params": {
        "command": "TRIG:A:EDGE:SOU CH1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_b_trigger_events",
      "title": "Set B Trigger to 5 Events After A",
      "params": {
        "command": "TRIG:B:EVENTS 5"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "error_check",
      "id": "check_errors",
      "title": "Check for Errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "id": "disconnect_scope",
      "title": "Disconnect from Oscilloscope"
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow will:

1. Connect to the oscilloscope.
2. Set the trigger type to Sequence (A-B).
3. Set the A trigger source to Channel 1.
4. Set the B trigger to occur 5 events after A.
5. Check for errors.
6. Disconnect from the oscilloscope.

If you need to further customize the trigger conditions (such as edge type, level, etc.), let me know!

